full_text:
A narrow doorway which will naturally increase the velocity of any air movement might be a good place to set it.
Or an open window, a place my significant Other always had to be next to, might be a good place for it. 
And  of course outside , with the intake hole facing the prevailing winds.

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Snowfire Lioness &lt;SnowfireL@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;  A fan might work with this type of thing too, but it might make too much noise. I did get some fairly good files using a fan one hot summer, with the box, but the sound from the fan reached the mic, and it sounds like they are out in a wind storm, but it did make them a bit louder. sf
